---
const stats = [
  { number: "5+", label: "Years in Data" },
  { number: "200+", label: "Reports Built" },
  { number: "1B+", label: "Rows Analyzed" },
  { number: "500+", label: "DSA Problems" },
];
---

<section id="about" class="py-24 md:py-32">
  <div class="max-w-[1280px] mx-auto px-6 md:px-8">
    <div class="mb-16">
      <span class="eyebrow text-ink/40 dark:text-dark-ink/40 mb-4 block reveal">About</span>
      <h2 class="display-lg max-w-[700px] text-ink dark:text-dark-ink reveal" style="transition-delay: 100ms">
        Data meets
        <span class="relative inline-block">
          <span class="relative z-10">intuition</span>
          <span class="absolute bottom-1 left-0 w-full h-3 bg-block-coral -z-0 rounded-sm"></span>
        </span>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-16 items-start">
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <p class="body-lg text-ink/70 dark:text-dark-ink/70 reveal" style="transition-delay: 100ms">
          I'm a data analyst who believes every dataset has a story — you just need the right lens to see it.
          My work sits at the intersection of statistical rigor and clear communication.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink/60 dark:text-dark-ink/60 reveal" style="transition-delay: 200ms">
          Over the past five years, I've built dashboards that drive executive decisions, designed ETL pipelines
          that process billions of rows, and delivered analyses that shaped product strategy at scale.
          I care about the whole picture — from the SQL query to the final stakeholder slide.
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink/60 dark:text-dark-ink/60 reveal" style="transition-delay: 300ms">
          Outside of analysis, I'm a vibe coder — I write scripts and tools that feel good to use, not just functional.
          I also grind DSA problems regularly because understanding algorithms sharpens how I think about
          data transformations and optimization at every level.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-4 reveal" style="transition-delay: 400ms">
          {["Python", "SQL", "Tableau", "Pandas", "Power BI", "Excel", "R", "dbt"].map((tag) => (
            <span class="px-3 py-1.5 bg-surface-soft dark:bg-dark-surface rounded-pill text-body-sm text-ink/70 dark:text-dark-ink/70 font-mono text-xs tracking-wider uppercase border border-hairline dark:border-dark-hairline">
              {tag}
            </span>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="relative reveal-right" style="transition-delay: 200ms">
        <div class="color-block-lilac grain relative overflow-hidden rounded-lg aspect-[4/5] flex items-end p-8">
          <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-block-navy/20 to-transparent"></div>
          <div class="relative z-10">
            <p class="headline text-ink dark:text-dark-ink">
              "The best analysis doesn't just answer questions — it reveals the ones nobody thought to ask."
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="absolute -top-4 -right-4 w-20 h-20 bg-block-mint rounded-full float-anim opacity-60"></div>
        <div class="absolute -bottom-3 -left-3 w-14 h-14 bg-block-lime rounded-full float-anim opacity-50" style="animation-delay: 1s"></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-8 mt-20 stagger-children">
      {stats.map((stat) => (
        <div class="reveal text-center md:text-left">
          <div class="display-lg mb-1 text-ink dark:text-dark-ink">{stat.number}</div>
          <div class="caption text-ink/40 dark:text-dark-ink/40">{stat.label}</div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
